            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, combine the Dijon, apple cider vinegar, dried dill and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;olive oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong>&nbsp;generously with salt and pepper and mix well to combine</p>\r\n<p><strong>This</strong> is your dressing</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cut</strong> the grapes in half</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the celery stick<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the spring onions finely, discarding the root ends</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the halloumi in half, lengthways, so you end up with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>&nbsp;slices</p>\r\n<p><strong>Boil</strong> another kettle (used in step 5)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Bash</strong> the walnuts to break them up (in the bag with a rolling pin)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a dry, non-stick pan</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the bashed walnuts and cook on a medium-low heat for 4 min or until toasted</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the toasted walnuts to a plate and set aside, then wipe the pan clean for step 7</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/326-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
